'Topic20240308-20240313':about blender and animation in blender


1.the basic workFlow right now im using in blender

the basic workFlow contains as follow
1.get the model mesh and retopology it use the addon quadMesher or whatever retopology tool(this step is to make the model can be calculate to a rig), maybe this can be done by using the new addon auto-rig.

2.create the rig armature.

3.create the motion or import the motion use the tech below

4.bind the mesh to the armature

(5.)maybe more steps including the bake texture uv need to be consider to be done.


2.the animation techFlow so far
use mmRig addon to import the mixamo animation into a mmd like rigify armature[1][2]
so far the vmp that is the mmd animation file cannot be import use the mmRig addon to import

the vmp to mixamo and finally to rigify is seems to be in this resource[3]


